        <section id="about" class="section">
            <h2>About Budha Kedar Nath Temple</h2>
            <p>
                The Budha Kedar Nath Temple is situated in the quaint village of Budha Kedar, about 59 kilometers from the district headquarters 
                of Tehri. The temple is nestled amidst lush green hills and the confluence of the rivers Bal Ganga and Dharam Ganga, making it 
                a picturesque and tranquil location. The temple architecture reflects the traditional Garhwali style and has a timeless charm.
            </p>
            <p>
                Visitors to the temple not only seek blessings but also enjoy the natural beauty and peaceful surroundings. The temple's 
                annual fair during the Shivaratri festival is a major event that attracts a large number of devotees and tourists.
            </p>
        </section>

